&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://media2.dev.to/dynamic/image/width=800%2Cheight=%2Cfit=scale-down%2Cgravity=auto%2Cformat=auto/https%3A%2F%2Fdev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fuploads%2Farticles%2Fg3beepec9z9jwzi9dzzh.png" class="article-body-image-wrapper"&gt;&lt;img src="https://media2.dev.to/dynamic/image/width=800%2Cheight=%2Cfit=scale-down%2Cgravity=auto%2Cformat=auto/https%3A%2F%2Fdev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fuploads%2Farticles%2Fg3beepec9z9jwzi9dzzh.png" alt="(Source: CertiProf)" width="800" height="450"&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (Photo Source: CertiProf)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Not all prompting techniques are equal. Each produces different behavioral responses.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using the wrong technique may cause:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hallucinations&lt;/li&gt;
