&lt;h2&gt;


  Core Prompting Techniques
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;


  1. Role Prompting
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Assign a role to shape tone, expertise, and reasoning.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;


  Template
&lt;/h3&gt;



&lt;div class="highlight js-code-highlight"&gt;
&lt;pre class="highlight plaintext"&gt;&lt;code&gt;Role: [Assign a role]

Task: [Define the task]

Context: [Provide necessary data]

Constraint: [Define limitations]
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;



&lt;h3&gt;


  Example (Software Development)
&lt;/h3&gt;



&lt;div class="highlight js-code-highlight"&gt;
&lt;pre class="highlight plaintext"&gt;&lt;code&gt;Role: Act as a Senior Frontend Developer who mentors junior developers.

Task: Review my CSS code below. I am trying to center a "Profile Card"
perfectly in the middle of the web page.

Context:
.background-container {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
}

Constraint: You are strictly forbidden from giving me the missing CSS
properties. Instead, explain the difference between the "main axis" and the
"cross axis" in Flexbox. Then ask me one guiding question.
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

